THOG2 stores compact spectral coefficients and materialises dense-equivalent transformer weights when they are needed. The Remainder Architecture Enhancement adds a second learned representation: one signed low-bit remainder code for each remainder-enabled materialised weight position.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af9\langfe2052\ql\fi0\li180\lin180\ri180\rin180\sb100\sa170\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf19\brsp0\brdrl\brdrs\brdrw25\brdrcf19\brsp0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf19\brsp0\brdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf19\brsp0\ltrpar\cbpat21{\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang3081\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\cf18\fs22\lang3081\b\kerning1\f4\dbch\af8\langfe2052\loch
A single weight consumed by the transformer\line remainder_offset = decode_remainder_offset(base_weight, remainder_value)\line effective_weight = base_weight + remainder_offset}
